10/08/2007
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Police arrested six people Thursday (August 9th) in Sisak, Zagreb and Zadar.
They are believed to be part of a gang involved in smuggling cocaine to Greece.
The sting, conducted with the help of Austrian police, reportedly uncovered heroin, cocaine, amphetamines, guns, false documents and foreign currency.
In other news, Albania's Shekulli newspaper reported on Friday that prosecutors are investigating 12 people, including six police officers, believed to be involved in a human trafficking network.
Dozens of people reportedly paid 500 euros apiece to be smuggled to Greece.
(Shekulli - 10/08/07;
HINA, HRT-- 09/08/07)
